Overview

Implemented the initial real-time communication infrastructure for the SyncSpace project using Express.js and Socket.io. This serves as the foundation for future collaborative features such as the whiteboard, code editor synchronization, and multi-user workspace.

Features Implemented
  
Express Server Setup
Configured Express application.
Added JSON middleware.
Enabled CORS support.
Added health check endpoint (/).
  
Socket.io Integration
Created HTTP server using Express.
Integrated Socket.io with the HTTP server.
Configured CORS for socket connections.
Established real-time client-server communication.

Socket Connection Management
Handled client connections.
Handled client disconnections.
Logged active socket connections for debugging.

Room Management

Implemented room-based collaboration.

Features:

Join Room
Leave Room
Multiple isolated rooms
Automatic room cleanup
Participant tracking

Room Service

Created a dedicated RoomService for managing collaborative sessions.

Responsibilities:

Create room
Add user
Remove user
Delete empty room
Get room participants

